1
00:00:06,180 --> 00:00:07,819
Thank you

2
00:00:07,820 --> 00:00:09,820
for agreeing to this interview.

3
00:00:10,140 --> 00:00:11,679
It's my honor

4
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:12,739
(Interview with Mr. Shen Gu,
founder of Qingniao Group)

5
00:00:12,740 --> 00:00:14,140
to be interviewed by you, Miss Xu.

6
00:00:16,780 --> 00:00:17,900
Wanxin,

7
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:22,380
can you ask Mr. Gu
to face the camera?

8
00:00:28,900 --> 00:00:32,099
Today, we'll be discussing

9
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:35,379
Qingniao's founding vision
and its core business philosophy.

10
00:00:35,380 --> 00:00:37,019
Starting from self-media,

11
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:40,019
you have successfully transitioned
into a leader in AI.

12
00:00:40,020 --> 00:00:41,139
Your insights

13
00:00:41,140 --> 00:00:44,300
will be highly valuable
to others in the industry.

14
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:46,420
Shall we begin?

15
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:48,579
Of course.

16
00:00:48,580 --> 00:00:49,379
Mr. Shen,

17
00:00:49,380 --> 00:00:51,699
I believe many loyal users of Qingniao

18
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:55,340
are curious about the story
behind the company's name.

19
00:00:55,620 --> 00:00:56,979
There's a line by Li Shangyin,

20
00:00:56,980 --> 00:00:59,060
"Would the blue birds
fly to see you on the height?"

21
00:00:59,420 --> 00:01:01,339
I hope every Qingniao user

22
00:01:01,340 --> 00:01:03,419
can capture the most meaningful moments

23
00:01:03,420 --> 00:01:04,499
in their lives

24
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:06,140
and share them with others.

25
00:01:07,220 --> 00:01:09,540
A blend of rationality and poetry.

26
00:01:09,980 --> 00:01:11,619
I enjoy using code

27
00:01:11,620 --> 00:01:14,020
to build bridges beyond reality.

28
00:01:14,340 --> 00:01:18,020
We all know AI demands immense effort.

29
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:21,379
What made you step out
of your comfort zone

30
00:01:21,380 --> 00:01:23,420
and push for this transformation?

31
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:25,260
I had a mentor

32
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:27,940
who has always guided me.

33
00:01:30,580 --> 00:01:32,020
He once said

34
00:01:32,220 --> 00:01:36,060
that turning creativity into products
is just the beginning.

35
00:01:36,380 --> 00:01:38,379
The real test for a company

36
00:01:38,380 --> 00:01:40,340
is how to turn user experience

37
00:01:40,380 --> 00:01:42,860
into something users truly value.

38
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:45,579
The user-centric approach

39
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:48,179
is the principle Qingniao follows

40
00:01:48,180 --> 00:01:49,820
in developing every product.

41
00:01:50,420 --> 00:01:51,739
At the same time,

42
00:01:51,740 --> 00:01:53,020
he also recognized early on

43
00:01:53,180 --> 00:01:55,740
the importance of tech patent research.

44
00:01:55,940 --> 00:01:56,859
When others

45
00:01:56,860 --> 00:01:59,540
were hesitant to invest heavily...

46
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:02,300
It was Zhaoming.

47
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:05,300
It's this spirit

48
00:02:05,540 --> 00:02:08,700
that lets us feel
his passion and belief.

49
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,759
And that's the reason Qingniao exists.

50
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:15,160
=Echoes of Gang City=

51
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:20,920
=Episode 20=
(Husband and Guest)

52
00:02:23,300 --> 00:02:24,740
He's truly someone

53
00:02:25,460 --> 00:02:27,180
worth learning from.

54
00:02:30,420 --> 00:02:32,819
Mr. Shen, could you share

55
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:35,779
the challenges Qingniao faced
in its early days

56
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:37,660
and how you overcame them?

57
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:40,359
It would offer young people
who are starting a business

58
00:02:40,359 --> 00:02:43,740
or facing difficulties some new ideas.

59
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:47,980
Forget those onlookers.

60
00:02:48,060 --> 00:02:50,740
I wake up in the middle of the night
and feel like slapping myself.

61
00:02:51,420 --> 00:02:52,779
Back then,

62
00:02:52,780 --> 00:02:55,099
you drove Shen Gu, who had nothing,
out of Gang City.

63
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,860
How did he suddenly become

64
00:02:57,060 --> 00:02:59,580
the founder of Qingniao?

65
00:03:13,940 --> 00:03:15,699
In the early days,

66
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:17,420
Qingniao faced many challenges.

67
00:03:17,540 --> 00:03:19,139
On the technical side,

68
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:22,340
I had to rely on self-learning
to solve problems.

69
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:32,260
He solved technical issues
through self-thought?

70
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:34,620
Looks like

71
00:03:36,260 --> 00:03:37,940
Shen Gu is a genius.

72
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:39,380
Of course.

73
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:43,260
Well, even geniuses
need to make a living

74
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:44,540
before starting a business.

75
00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:33,540
Hey, bro.

76
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:35,400
I'm here to collect my assignment.

77
00:04:36,420 --> 00:04:37,499
I saved it on a USB.

78
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:38,780
Take it yourself.

79
00:04:39,020 --> 00:04:40,140
Oh.

80
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:42,779
I'm short on time.

81
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:44,420
I need to meet an investor.

82
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:46,060
Can you give me a ride?

83
00:04:47,660 --> 00:04:48,739
Let's go.

84
00:04:48,740 --> 00:04:49,860
Thank you.

85
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:54,780
Why are you knocking?

86
00:04:55,660 --> 00:04:57,219
Your garage is still open.

87
00:04:57,220 --> 00:04:59,139
Forget it.

88
00:04:59,140 --> 00:05:00,419
Can you drive faster?

89
00:05:00,420 --> 00:05:01,780
Or should I drive?

90
00:05:02,220 --> 00:05:03,540
I'm good at this.

91
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:14,380
This is my proposed
new distributed link algorithm.

92
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:17,260
It can improve
big data processing speed

93
00:05:17,340 --> 00:05:18,860
and reduce operating costs.

94
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:21,740
Here are my test results.

95
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:28,980
You built all this alone in your garage?

96
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:30,420
Yes.

97
00:05:30,860 --> 00:05:32,220
To be honest,

98
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:34,340
this technology is too advanced.

99
00:05:34,540 --> 00:05:36,340
It doesn't match current market needs.

100
00:05:36,620 --> 00:05:39,219
The architecture is too complex

101
00:05:39,220 --> 00:05:40,740
and carries significant risks.

102
00:05:41,060 --> 00:05:43,420
Being ahead of time
is exactly what gives it value.

103
00:05:43,620 --> 00:05:45,660
I can solve the engineering challenges.

104
00:05:45,820 --> 00:05:47,619
As long as I have enough
funding and time...

105
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:48,740
Young man,

106
00:05:49,220 --> 00:05:50,899
Raymond Group

107
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:53,340
invests heavily in R&amp;D every day.

108
00:05:54,420 --> 00:05:56,020
But why would we choose

109
00:05:56,220 --> 00:05:58,020
an unproven startup product

110
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:00,780
like yours?

111
00:06:06,540 --> 00:06:08,540
There are two things
the world doesn't lack.

112
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:12,420
Geniuses

113
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:13,740
and ideas.

114
00:06:14,220 --> 00:06:15,340
I'm sorry.

115
00:06:16,860 --> 00:06:19,020
This doesn't fit our investment logic.

116
00:06:27,820 --> 00:06:28,940
Wait.

117
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:33,860
I can offer you USD 100,000

118
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:37,140
to buy all your data and ideas.

119
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:02,260
Raymond Group was trying to
take advantage of the situation?

120
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:03,660
Raymond Group

121
00:07:04,420 --> 00:07:05,780
underestimated Shen Gu.

122
00:07:07,740 --> 00:07:10,219
These are topics
that were widely discussed

123
00:07:10,220 --> 00:07:11,940
on your campus forum.

124
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:14,699
People said during college,

125
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:17,059
you worked multiple jobs,

126
00:07:17,060 --> 00:07:20,180
even wrote assignments for others.

127
00:07:20,820 --> 00:07:23,260
Is that true?

128
00:07:24,940 --> 00:07:28,580
Server costs were very expensive
back then.

129
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:36,860
Aside from that, what do you think

130
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,880
was the most important fact
behind your success?

131
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:44,860
My business partner, Mr. Fang.

132
00:07:48,420 --> 00:07:51,260
Shen Gu, here you are.

133
00:07:53,220 --> 00:07:54,540
I want to hear about this.

134
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:58,340
Distributed architecture
for user-generated content.

135
00:07:58,940 --> 00:08:00,380
Where did you get this?

136
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:03,540
The investment club.

137
00:08:04,820 --> 00:08:06,220
What do you need

138
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,420
to make this happen?

139
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:10,299
I submitted a proposal
to the investment club.

140
00:08:10,300 --> 00:08:12,140
Needless to say, I need startup funding.

141
00:08:12,620 --> 00:08:13,980
Exactly.

142
00:08:14,060 --> 00:08:15,219
Come, Mr. Gu.

143
00:08:15,220 --> 00:08:16,099
Have a seat.

144
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,660
Sit.

145
00:08:18,820 --> 00:08:20,859
We'll register the company tomorrow.

146
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:22,619
You handle the tech patents,

147
00:08:22,620 --> 00:08:24,899
I'll take care
of all the startup funding.

148
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:27,020
Fifty-fifty shares.

149
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:33,899
Fine. I'll take 30, you take 70.

150
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:35,059
From today on,

151
00:08:35,060 --> 00:08:37,219
you're the CTO and CEO.

152
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:38,819
I'll be the CFO. I study law.

153
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:40,499
I can also handle legal for you.

154
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,219
We can definitely build something

155
00:08:42,220 --> 00:08:44,940
like Raymond Group.

156
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:56,260
How much have you drunk?

157
00:08:56,860 --> 00:08:58,940
I drove here.

158
00:09:00,220 --> 00:09:03,140
I think we should go grab a drink now.

159
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:04,420
Let's go.

160
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:05,580
Come on.

161
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:10,140
He's also my best friend.

162
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,740
Honestly,

163
00:09:28,380 --> 00:09:31,020
since he got married,
he's gotten kind of cheesy.

164
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:40,400
(Su Mei: Congrats, someone
confessed to you, Mr. Fang)

165
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,460
I'm really glad

166
00:09:48,820 --> 00:09:50,620
you have a friend like him.

167
00:10:03,140 --> 00:10:04,860
What's this show supposed to be?

168
00:10:05,060 --> 00:10:07,979
A finance interview, or a dating show?

169
00:10:07,980 --> 00:10:09,180
Tomorrow,

170
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:10,940
this is definitely going to blow up.

171
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,660
That's all for today's interview.

172
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:15,660
Thank you, Mr. Shen.

173
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:18,860
Thank you, everyone. See you.

174
00:10:29,740 --> 00:10:31,060
Good job.

175
00:10:33,020 --> 00:10:34,140
Let's go home.

176
00:10:42,660 --> 00:10:43,619
Off work!

177
00:10:43,620 --> 00:10:45,059
Off work!

178
00:10:45,060 --> 00:10:45,699
Let's go.

179
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:47,900
Let's go.

180
00:10:48,060 --> 00:10:48,979
Good work, everyone.

181
00:10:48,980 --> 00:10:50,180
Let's go home.

182
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:53,339
Hey, what are you doing?

183
00:10:53,340 --> 00:10:54,579
Off you go.

184
00:10:54,580 --> 00:10:55,699
Let's go.

185
00:10:55,700 --> 00:10:56,739
No more gossiping.

186
00:10:56,740 --> 00:10:58,580
Let's go.

187
00:10:58,810 --> 00:10:59,619
I'm so jealous.

188
00:10:59,620 --> 00:11:01,339
Lawyer Fang, you're not leaving?

189
00:11:01,340 --> 00:11:03,060
Is this ever going to end?

190
00:11:06,940 --> 00:11:09,460
A carefully planned finance interview

191
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:11,939
has cast Shen Gu as a victim
of our persecution,

192
00:11:11,940 --> 00:11:14,260
who endured hardships overseas

193
00:11:14,620 --> 00:11:16,820
and ultimately came back
as a successful entrepreneur.

194
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:18,780
Fine.

195
00:11:19,620 --> 00:11:21,220
If he wants the spotlight so much,

196
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:23,980
let him have it.

197
00:11:24,620 --> 00:11:27,900
Now is not the time to fight
public opinion.

198
00:11:28,260 --> 00:11:32,260
Focus on the shareholders' meeting.

199
00:11:33,620 --> 00:11:37,140
Raymond is the key to winning.

200
00:11:37,340 --> 00:11:40,060
The spotlight is on us now.

201
00:11:40,820 --> 00:11:43,340
Now we're the ones getting attacked.

202
00:11:43,820 --> 00:11:45,540
Since I chose to do this,

203
00:11:45,860 --> 00:11:47,580
I'm not afraid of being criticized.

204
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:49,979
Honestly,

205
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:52,140
you were too soft back then.

206
00:11:55,178 --> 00:11:58,018
You should've just killed all of them.

207
00:11:58,340 --> 00:11:59,980
Stop right there.

208
00:12:00,340 --> 00:12:01,740
You can mess around here,

209
00:12:02,060 --> 00:12:05,420
and I'll cover for you.

210
00:12:06,220 --> 00:12:07,860
But if it involves lives,

211
00:12:08,460 --> 00:12:09,940
no one can save you.

212
00:12:11,420 --> 00:12:14,380
You've always looked down on me.

213
00:12:31,260 --> 00:12:33,180
Hello, Mr. Lei Meng.

214
00:12:33,420 --> 00:12:35,380
We've seen Shen Gu's interview.

215
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:38,099
Your PR team should
really learn from it.

216
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:39,940
Compared to your tabloid tactics,

217
00:12:40,620 --> 00:12:42,619
mainstream media

218
00:12:42,620 --> 00:12:44,180
is far more convincing.

219
00:12:44,620 --> 00:12:45,940
Mr. Lei Meng,

220
00:12:46,420 --> 00:12:50,500
did you call just to mock me?

221
00:12:53,540 --> 00:12:55,980
No, I have good news for you.

222
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:29,660
Wanxin.

223
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:32,900
Don't come closer.

224
00:13:33,140 --> 00:13:34,740
Watch out for the glass.

225
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:47,540
Why are your hands so cold?

226
00:13:48,820 --> 00:13:50,020
I just...

227
00:13:52,220 --> 00:13:53,420
I remembered something

228
00:13:54,620 --> 00:13:56,180
from the past.

229
00:13:58,540 --> 00:13:59,460
Look at this.

230
00:14:01,620 --> 00:14:03,060
Why are you here?

231
00:14:03,820 --> 00:14:06,540
Don't you hate us?

232
00:14:07,740 --> 00:14:10,180
For the sake of my dad
helping build Junlin,

233
00:14:10,620 --> 00:14:11,820
I'm here to beg you

234
00:14:12,420 --> 00:14:14,020
to let my mom and me live.

235
00:14:14,540 --> 00:14:16,060
She's in critical condition.

236
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:17,740
She needs money for surgery.

237
00:14:20,540 --> 00:14:23,739
She tells everyone that your dad died
because of me,

238
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:25,259
and ruins my reputation.

239
00:14:25,260 --> 00:14:26,940
I won't help her.

240
00:14:27,540 --> 00:14:28,980
As long as she survives this,

241
00:14:29,060 --> 00:14:30,380
we'll leave Gang City.

242
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:34,019
Dad, why are you wasting time
on this beggar?

243
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:35,059
I'm a beggar?

244
00:14:35,060 --> 00:14:37,059
I'm just taking back
what belongs to my family.

245
00:14:37,060 --> 00:14:41,099
You built your fortune on my dad's work,
then turned on us and went all out to ruin us.

246
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:41,859
If...

247
00:14:41,860 --> 00:14:43,499
If you don't leave us a way out,

248
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:45,219
then no one walks away.

249
00:14:45,220 --> 00:14:46,899
I'll expose everything

250
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:49,260
you've done to my family.

251
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:15,620
From a famous singer to this.

252
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:17,219
In Gang City,

253
00:15:17,220 --> 00:15:18,859
going against the Shen family

254
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:20,139
without power or backing,

255
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:21,820
there's something to admire.

256
00:15:22,420 --> 00:15:24,619
But if we don't operate now,

257
00:15:24,620 --> 00:15:26,300
she won't make it through today.

258
00:15:32,940 --> 00:15:34,459
Boy, it's about to rain.

259
00:15:34,460 --> 00:15:36,020
Go inside.

260
00:15:43,060 --> 00:15:44,259
Forget the surgery.

261
00:15:44,260 --> 00:15:46,099
He hasn't even paid the medical bill

262
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,699
for over a month.

263
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:49,020
So pitiful.

264
00:16:04,620 --> 00:16:05,980
It's going to rain.

265
00:16:06,020 --> 00:16:07,780
Your wound might get infected.

266
00:16:16,660 --> 00:16:19,540
The surgery and medical fees
have been paid for.

267
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:33,819
I'll pay you

268
00:16:33,820 --> 00:16:34,579
back.

269
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:35,740
Alright.

270
00:16:35,820 --> 00:16:36,980
What's your name?

271
00:16:37,100 --> 00:16:38,380
Xu Wanxin.

272
00:16:42,340 --> 00:16:44,460
Thank you, Xu Wanxin.

273
00:16:55,820 --> 00:16:56,699
Miss,

274
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:58,139
this is the payment slip for Ward 3.

275
00:16:58,140 --> 00:17:00,340
Can we arrange the surgery now?
Hurry, please.

276
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:02,340
Quick! Patient in Bed 3 is critical!

277
00:17:03,220 --> 00:17:04,340
Three...

278
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:10,620
Slow down.

279
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:16,740
Please wait outside.

280
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:27,260
We're very sorry.

281
00:17:28,580 --> 00:17:30,340
We did everything we could.

282
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:50,540
Mom!

283
00:18:10,180 --> 00:18:11,300
From now on,

284
00:18:12,980 --> 00:18:15,020
I'll always stay by your side.

285
00:18:32,660 --> 00:18:37,590
♪The clouds hide the faint light
behind them♪

286
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:42,690
♪A lonely bench on the street corner♪

287
00:18:43,030 --> 00:18:47,040
♪Where all feelings come to rest♪

288
00:18:48,330 --> 00:18:52,429
♪In the night sky, the moon's trail♪

289
00:18:52,430 --> 00:18:56,419
♪Stitches up and soothes my sorrow♪

290
00:18:56,420 --> 00:18:59,299
♪The courage to get close to you♪

291
00:18:59,300 --> 00:19:02,930
♪Drives away my hesitation♪

292
00:19:03,650 --> 00:19:05,899
♪Fate turns and brings us together♪

293
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:07,889
♪I search my memories with all my might♪

294
00:19:07,890 --> 00:19:10,799
♪Love catches me off guard♪

295
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:12,949
♪You, in the album♪

296
00:19:12,950 --> 00:19:18,130
♪Shine through my past like starlight♪

297
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:22,369
♪You fall between light and shadow♪

298
00:19:22,370 --> 00:19:26,319
♪Melting all my fears away♪

299
00:19:26,320 --> 00:19:30,109
♪Those youthful, naive memories
are more than enough to heal♪

300
00:19:30,110 --> 00:19:32,770
♪I'm lost in them♪

301
00:19:55,920 --> 00:20:01,720
♪Tonight the rain falls soft and slow♪

302
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:08,800
♪Blending with letters left unread
drifting through the air♪

303
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:14,880
♪You turn and look back at me♪

304
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:21,520
♪In those same eyes familiar tears
quietly appear♪

305
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:28,000
♪It feels like we have carried so much♪

306
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:34,760
♪So many questions time itself
could not make clear♪

307
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:41,200
♪The moment you walked into my life♪

308
00:20:42,360 --> 00:20:48,160
♪Every dream I had became something
I want with you near♪

309
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:55,520
♪How many letters have I written
just for you?♪

310
00:20:55,640 --> 00:21:01,320
♪If only you could truly hear
what my heart is trying to say♪

311
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:08,359
♪From this life on
no distance could keep us apart♪

312
00:21:08,360 --> 00:21:11,239
♪The promise we made♪

313
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:14,919
♪Will find its way to be fulfilled
one day♪

314
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:21,519
♪But I want more
than just that fleeting gaze♪

315
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:27,920
♪Still I have not heard your answer♪

316
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:34,639
♪Can we still rewrite the ending
we face?♪

317
00:21:34,640 --> 00:21:39,760
♪When regrets begin to turn around you
will hear it all♪

318
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:43,240
♪Everything that leads me back to you♪
